==English==

===Etymology===
Old English ''[[elm#Old English|elm]]'', from Germanic ''*elmaz'', from Indo-European.  Cognate with dialectal German ''[[Ilm]]'', Swedish ''[[alm]]''; and (''from Indo-European'') with Latin ''[[ulmus]]''.

===Pronunciation===
* {{AHD|ĕlm}}, {{IPA|/ɛlm/}}, {{SAMPA|/elm/}}
* Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɛlm|-ɛlm]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

#a tree of the genus ''[[Ulmus]]'' of the family ''[[Ulmaceae]]'', large [[deciduous]] trees with alternate [[stipulate]] leaves and small [[apetalous]] flowers
#(usually attributive) wood from an elm tree

